---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Word & Character Counter"
  description="Count words, characters, sentences, paragraphs, and estimate reading time. Free online tool with real-time counting."
>
  <div id="word-counter-app">
    <textarea
      id="wc-input"
      rows="10"
      placeholder="Type or paste your text here..."
      class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-base resize-y focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500 focus:border-transparent"
    ></textarea>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-5 gap-4 mt-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div id="wc-words" class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-600">0</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Words</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div id="wc-chars" class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-600">0</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Characters</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div id="wc-chars-no-space" class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-600">0</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">No Spaces</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div id="wc-sentences" class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-600">0</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Sentences</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div id="wc-paragraphs" class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-600">0</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Paragraphs</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex gap-4 mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
      <span>Reading time: <strong id="wc-reading-time">0 min</strong></span>
      <span>Speaking time: <strong id="wc-speaking-time">0 min</strong></span>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 flex gap-3">
      <button id="wc-copy" class="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-indigo-700 transition-colors">
        Copy Text
      </button>
      <button id="wc-clear" class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-gray-300 transition-colors">
        Clear
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SEO Content -->
  <div class="mt-12 prose prose-sm max-w-none">
    <h2>Free Online Word Counter Tool</h2>
    <p>Count words, characters, sentences, and paragraphs instantly as you type. Our word counter tool provides real-time statistics including reading time and speaking time estimates. Perfect for writers, students, bloggers, and content creators.</p>

    <h3>Features</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Real-time counting</strong> - Statistics update instantly as you type</li>
      <li><strong>Character count</strong> - With and without spaces</li>
      <li><strong>Reading time</strong> - Based on average 200 WPM reading speed</li>
      <li><strong>Speaking time</strong> - Based on average 130 WPM speaking speed</li>
      <li><strong>No sign-up required</strong> - Just paste and count</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How to Use the Word Counter</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3 text-gray-600">
      <li><strong>Paste or type your text</strong> — Enter your text into the input area. All statistics update automatically in real time as you type.</li>
      <li><strong>View your word count</strong> — Check the word, character, sentence, and paragraph counts displayed below the input area.</li>
      <li><strong>Check reading and speaking time</strong> — See estimated reading time (based on 200 WPM) and speaking time (based on 130 WPM) for your text.</li>
      <li><strong>Copy or clear</strong> — Use the Copy button to copy your text to clipboard, or Clear to start over with new text.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">How does the word counter calculate word count?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">The tool splits your text by whitespace characters (spaces, tabs, line breaks) and counts each resulting segment as a word. This matches the standard word counting method used by most text editors and word processors.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">What is the difference between characters and characters without spaces?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">The "Characters" count includes every character in your text including spaces, while "No Spaces" counts only non-whitespace characters. Many platforms like Twitter count all characters, while others like some SMS services only count non-space characters.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">How accurate is the reading time estimate?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">The reading time is calculated using an average adult reading speed of 200 words per minute. Actual reading speed varies by person and content complexity, but this is the standard benchmark used by platforms like Medium and WordPress.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Can I use this tool for essay word count limits?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Yes, this tool is perfect for checking if your essay, assignment, or article meets specific word count requirements. It counts words in real time, so you can see exactly when you hit your target as you write or edit.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Does the word counter work with all languages?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">The word counter works with any language that uses spaces to separate words, including English, Spanish, French, German, and more. For languages like Chinese or Japanese that do not use spaces between words, the character count will be accurate but the word count may not reflect actual word boundaries.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

<script>
  const input = document.getElementById('wc-input') as HTMLTextAreaElement;
  const wordsEl = document.getElementById('wc-words')!;
  const charsEl = document.getElementById('wc-chars')!;
  const charsNoSpaceEl = document.getElementById('wc-chars-no-space')!;
  const sentencesEl = document.getElementById('wc-sentences')!;
  const paragraphsEl = document.getElementById('wc-paragraphs')!;
  const readingTimeEl = document.getElementById('wc-reading-time')!;
  const speakingTimeEl = document.getElementById('wc-speaking-time')!;

  function update() {
    const text = input.value;
    const words = text.trim() === '' ? 0 : text.trim().split(/\s+/).length;
    const chars = text.length;
    const charsNoSpace = text.replace(/\s/g, '').length;
    const sentences = text.trim() === '' ? 0 : text.split(/[.!?]+/).filter(s => s.trim()).length;
    const paragraphs = text.trim() === '' ? 0 : text.split(/\n\s*\n/).filter(p => p.trim()).length;
    const readingMin = Math.ceil(words / 200);
    const speakingMin = Math.ceil(words / 130);

    wordsEl.textContent = String(words);
    charsEl.textContent = String(chars);
    charsNoSpaceEl.textContent = String(charsNoSpace);
    sentencesEl.textContent = String(sentences);
    paragraphsEl.textContent = String(paragraphs);
    readingTimeEl.textContent = `${readingMin} min`;
    speakingTimeEl.textContent = `${speakingMin} min`;
  }

  input.addEventListener('input', update);

  document.getElementById('wc-copy')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(input.value);
  });

  document.getElementById('wc-clear')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    input.value = '';
    update();
  });
</script>
